{
    "name": "Goblin Firestarter",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Tactics",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>During Combat</b> A firestarter avoids melee, instead making sneak attacks with its bow and using alchemist\u2019s fire or <i>flaming</i> arrows to start fires, cause panic, and trap opponents. It saves its <i>goblin skull bomb</i> for a weak opponent, hoping to kill that foe and craft a new <i>goblin skull bomb</i> from the corpse."
        },
        {
            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> temperate forest and plains (usually coastal regions)"
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Goblins adore theft, and are adept at slinking about undetected. Goblin sneaks are master ambushers and spectacular hiders. The most talented also incorporate their racial love of fire into their tactics."
        }
    ],
